    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="745"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d745">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Williams</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-14">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">November</hi> 14, 1895</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1180.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose, with further reference to the case of
                    Julio Sanguily, a copy of a letter addressed to the Department by his brother,
                    Manuel Sanguily, in which he requests that you may be present at the trial
                    which, as you report, has been set down for the 28th of this month.</p>
                <p>You will accordingly attend the public proceedings as a spectator and make
                    concise but sufficient report thereof to this Department.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Assistant Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
